      "problem": "A diagnostic accuracy study was assessed against STROBE (observational study guideline) rather than STARD (diagnostic accuracy reporting guideline).",
      "root_cause": "Study design classification before guideline selection exists but STARD is not included in the current guideline coverage.",
      "fix": "Add STARD to the supported guidelines and add a design-to-guideline mapping: diagnostic accuracy → STARD; RCT → CONSORT; observational → STROBE; systematic review/meta-analysis → PRISMA; prediction model → TRIPOD."
    },
    {
      "priority": "P2",
      "title": "No guidance on how to handle updated versions of reporting guidelines",
      "observed_in": [],
      "problem": "Reporting guidelines (especially CONSORT, PRISMA) have multiple versions. The skill does not specify which version to apply.",
      "root_cause": "Guideline version specification not included.",
      "fix": "Add a version specification note: use the most recent published version of each guideline. Note the version used in the output. When in doubt, verify on the guideline's official website."
